      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "LIGHTNING QUICK (4) flew the lids off the inside draw with a fast early split and gave a sight, finishing a half a length second (43.16) over 730m at The Meadows. The form out of the last run is proven to be strong. Can measure up this time. SLICK NITRO (8) goes very well at this course having never missed the frame including three wins. Comes off a (42.65) win last time, scoring by 3.5 lengths in a Grade 5 over 730m at The Meadows. Can feature with the right run. JONI BLACK (5) stalked the pace from a low draw last start and fought on well to finish 7 lengths away in second (38.18) at Ballarat in a Grade 5 over 660m. Didn't win last time but still ran one of the quickest times on the card. Bold showing expected. PAW GRADY (1) is worth another chance despite missing the top-three here most recently.",
